$ ls -al = list all files in long format and with hidden files

ex:
alias lh='ls -alh' ->this alias is available in this session only
$ alias = shows all defined aliases in the session
$ unalias lh = removes alias

-> make alias permanent
$ echo "alias lh='ls -alh'" >> .bashrc = adds it to the file .bashrc

->we need to load the file into the ession to use the alias
$ source ./.bashrc = reads and executes scripts (content of the files, as it doesn't need to be script) in current shell



if [ -f ~/.bash_aliases ]; then
    . ~/.bash_aliases
fi

$ echo "alias lh1='ls -alh'" >> .bash_aliases
$ source ./.bashrc

->aliases for other users
-we add them here : /etc/profile.d
$ echo "alias lh2='ls -alh'" >> /etc/profile.d/99-aliases.sh
